Tell a story about explaining a Phishing attempt. Who is doing it? to whom? why? Is it recognized? why or why not?

An email can be used for reading messages sent by people and companies. However someone can get in to the email account send mail to get a person's information. This is called phishing. Pretend someone leaked his email address online. A cyberattacker can send an email about a company the person knows and can trick him into clicking a link. Once the attacker gets hold of the address, (s)he can make a fake email explaining about important information and provide a link ccontaining ahacked site that steals the person's information that the hacker can get a hold of.
